quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  16,51,"And Allah has said, ‚ÄúDo not take two gods. There is only One God. So be in awe of Me ňĻaloneňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  16,52,"To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth, and to Him ňĻaloneňļ is the everlasting devotion. Will you then fear any other than Allah"
  16,53,"Whatever blessings you have are from Allah. Then whenever hardship touches you, to Him ňĻaloneňļ you cry ňĻfor helpňļ"
  16,54,"Then as soon as He removes the hardship from you, a group of you associates ňĻothersňļ with their Lord ňĻin worshipňļ"
  16,55,"only returning Our favours with ingratitude. So enjoy yourselves, for you will soon know"
  16,56,And they ňĻevenňļ assign to those ňĻidolsňļ‚ÄĒwho know nothing‚ÄĒa share of what We have provided for them. By Allah! You will certainly be questioned about whatever ňĻliesňļ you used to fabricate ňĻagainst Allahňļ
  16,57,And they attribute ňĻangels asňļ daughters to Allah‚ÄĒglory be to Him!‚ÄĒthe opposite of what they desire for themselves
  16,58,"Whenever one of them is given the good news of a baby girl, his face grows gloomy, as he suppresses his rage"
  16,59,"He hides himself from the people because of the bad news he has received. Should he keep her in disgrace, or bury her ňĻaliveňļ in the ground? Evil indeed is their judgment"
  16,60,"To those who disbelieve in the Hereafter belong all evil qualities, whereas to Allah belong the finest attributes. And He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  16,61,"If Allah were to punish people ňĻimmediatelyňļ for their wrongdoing, He would not have left a single living being on earth. But He delays them for an appointed term. And when their time arrives, they cannot delay it for a moment, nor could they advance it"
  16,62,"They attribute to Allah what they hate ňĻfor themselvesňļ,¬†and their tongues utter the lie that they will have the finest reward. Without a doubt, for them is the Fire, where they will be abandoned"
  16,63,"By Allah! We have surely sent messengers to communities before you ňĻO Prophetňļ, but Satan made their misdeeds appealing to them. So he is their patron today, and they will suffer a painful punishment"
  16,64,"We have revealed to you the Book only to clarify for them what they differed about, and as a guide and mercy for those who believe"
  16,65,"And Allah sends down rain from the sky, giving life to the earth after its death. Surely in this is a sign for those who listen"
  16,66,"And there is certainly a lesson for you in cattle: We give you to drink of what is in their bellies, from between digested food and blood: pure milk, pleasant to drink"
  16,67,And from the fruits of palm trees and grapevines you derive intoxicants¬†as well as wholesome provision. Surely in this is a sign for those who understand
  16,68,"And your Lord inspired the bees: ‚ÄúMake ňĻyourňļ homes in the mountains, the trees, and in what people construct"
  16,69,"and feed from ňĻthe flower ofňļ any fruit ňĻyou pleaseňļ and follow the ways your Lord has made easy for you.‚ÄĚ From their bellies comes forth liquid of varying colours, in which there is healing for people. Surely in this is a sign for those who reflect"
  16,70,"Allah has created you, and then causes you to die. And some of you are left to reach the most feeble stage of life so that they may know nothing after having known much. Indeed, Allah is All-Knowing, Most Capable"
  16,71,"And Allah has favoured some of you over others in provision. But those who have been much favoured would not share their wealth with those ňĻbondspeopleňļ in their possession, making them their equals.¬†Do they then deny Allah‚Äôs favours"
  16,72,"And Allah has made for you spouses of your own kind, and given you through your spouses children and grandchildren.¬†And He has granted you good, lawful provisions. Are they then faithful to falsehood and ungrateful for Allah‚Äôs favours"
  16,73,"Yet they worship besides Allah those ňĻidolsňļ who do not afford them any provision from the heavens and the earth, nor do they have the power to"
  16,74,"So do not set up equals to Allah, for Allah certainly knows and you do not know"